{"title_page": "Laurent Roux", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Laurent Roux\n| image         = Laurent ROUX.jpg\n| full_name     = Laurent Roux\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1972|12|03|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Cahors]], [[France]]\n| currentteam   = Retired\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 = 1992\n| amateurteam1  = US Montauban\n| proyears1     = 1994\n| proteam1      = Castorama-MaxiSport\n| proyears2     = 1995\n| proteam2      = Castorama\n| proyears3     = 1996\n| proteam3      = TVM\n| proyears4     = 1997&ndash;1998\n| proteam4      = TVM-Farm Frites\n| proyears5     = 1999\n| proteam5      = Casino\n| proyears6     = 2000\n| proteam6      = Mobilvetta Design-Rossin\n| proyears7     = 2001&ndash;2002\n| proteam7      = Jean Delatour\n| majorwins     = Giro d'Italia, 1 stage\n}}\n\n'''Laurent Roux''' (born 3 December 1972 in [[Cahors]]) is a [[French people|French]] former [[road bicycle racer]].\n\n==Doping==\nIn 1999, he was found guilty of using amphetamines and was suspended for six months.<ref name=LR1>{{cite web\n| title      = Cycling: Roux admits drug use and dealing\n| publisher  = www.iht.com\n| date       = 20 June 2006\n| url        = http://www.iht.com/articles/2006/06/20/sports/bike.php\n| accessdate = 22 November 2007 }}</ref> In 2002, he was tested non-negative for [[amphetamines]] after an out of competition control.<ref>{{cite web\n| title      = Laurent Roux non-negative for amphetamines\n| publisher  = www.cyclingnews.com\n| date       = 30 June 2002\n| url        = http://autobus.cyclingnews.com/road/2002/tour02/?id=news/jun02/jun30\n| accessdate = 22 November 2007 }}</ref> In 2006 he also confessed at a doping trial in Bordeaux that he used [[Erythropoietin|EPO]], [[human growth hormone]], [[cortisone]] and [[testosterone (medication)|testosterone]] and sold \"[[Pot Belge]]\" to other riders.<ref name=LR1/>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1996\n:1st, Stage 2b, [[Route du Sud]]\n;1997\n:1st, [[Classique des Alpes]]\n:1st, [[Paris\u2013Bourges]]\n:1st, Stage 3, [[Route du Sud]]\n:1st, Overall, [[Tour de l'Avenir]]\n;1998\n:1st, Stage 13, [[1998 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1999\n:1st, [[Troph\u00e9e des Grimpeurs]]\n:1st, Stage 4, [[Paris\u2013Nice]]\n;2001\n:1st, Stage 2, [[Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9|Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 Lib\u00e9r\u00e9]]\n:1st, Stage 3, [[Route du Sud]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of doping cases in cycling]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cyclingbase.com/palcoureurs.php?id=1472&idtitle=1 Palmar\u00e8s by cyclingbase.com] {{in lang|fr}}\n*{{CycleBase|13937}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Roux, Laurent}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Doping cases in cycling]]\n[[Category:French Giro d'Italia stage winners]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lot (department)]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1970s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Laurent Roux\n| image         = Laurent ROUX.jpg\n| full_name     = Laurent Roux\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1972|12|03|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Cahors]], [[France]]\n| currentteam   = Retired\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 = 1992\n| amateurteam1  = US Montauban\n| proyears1     = 1994\n| proteam1      = Castorama-MaxiSport\n| proyears2     = 1995\n| proteam2      = Castorama\n| proyears3     = 1996\n| proteam3      = TVM\n| proyears4     = 1997&ndash;1998\n| proteam4      = TVM-Farm Frites\n| proyears5     = 1999\n| proteam5      = Casino\n| proyears6     = 2000\n| proteam6      = Mobilvetta Design-Rossin\n| proyears7     = 2001&ndash;2002\n| proteam7      = Jean Delatour\n| majorwins     = Giro d'Italia, 1 stage\n}}\n\n'''Laurent Roux''' (born 3 December 1972 in [[Cahors]]) is a [[French people|French]] former [[road bicycle racer]].\n\n==Doping==\nIn 1999, he was found guilty of using amphetamines and was suspended for six months.<ref name=LR1>{{cite web\n| title      = Cycling: Roux admits drug use and dealing\n| publisher  = www.iht.com\n| date       = 20 June 2006\n| url        = http://www.iht.com/articles/2006/06/20/sports/bike.php\n| accessdate = 22 November 2007 }}</ref> In 2002, he was tested non-negative for [[amphetamines]] after an out of competition control.<ref>{{cite web\n| title      = Laurent Roux non-negative for amphetamines\n| publisher  = www.cyclingnews.com\n| date       = 30 June 2002\n| url        = http://autobus.cyclingnews.com/road/2002/tour02/?id=news/jun02/jun30\n| accessdate = 22 November 2007 }}</ref> In 2006 he also confessed at a doping trial in Bordeaux that he used [[Erythropoietin|EPO]], [[human growth hormone]], [[cortisone]] and [[testosterone (medication)|testosterone]] and sold \"[[Pot Belge]]\" to other riders.<ref name=LR1/>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1996\n:1st, Stage 2b, [[Route du Sud]]\n;1997\n:1st, [[Classique des Alpes]]\n:1st, [[Paris\u2013Bourges]]\n:1st, Stage 3, [[Route du Sud]]\n:1st, Overall, [[Tour de l'Avenir]]\n;1998\n:1st, Stage 13, [[1998 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1999\n:1st, [[Troph\u00e9e des Grimpeurs]]\n:1st, Stage 4, [[Paris\u2013Nice]]\n;2001\n:1st, Stage 2, [[Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9|Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 Lib\u00e9r\u00e9]]\n:1st, Stage 3, [[Route du Sud]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of doping cases in cycling]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cyclingbase.com/palcoureurs.php?id=1472&idtitle=1 Palmar\u00e8s by cyclingbase.com] {{in lang|fr}}\n*{{CycleBase|13937}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Roux, Laurent}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Doping 